        "created_at": "2025-06-30T22:00:45.841Z",
        "cooked": "<p>When someone posts a React to a message the text content of the notification is essentially “Bob sent a heart react to the message: <em>insert original text here</em>”.</p>\n<p>I understand the intention is to make it clear what they are reacting to, but when Siri announces the notification in my AirPods, what I constantly get is “Bob sent a long message.”</p>\n<p>Except that Bob didn’t send a long message. Bob just sent a heart react to -my- long message. It would be REALLY good if you could change the text of the react notification to something short enough that a) Siri will actually just read it and b) that it’s as short as sending a react is.</p>\n<p>“Bob reacted Heart” or<br>\n“Bob reacted with a Heart” or<br>\n“Bob reacted with a Heart to Joe’s message.”</p>\n<p>Or something like that, but short enough that it still gets read and I don’t need to fish out my phone, open Signal, find the chat, and then realize that Bob didn’t actually send a long message. Thank you!</p>",
